# ─── Rust / Tauri build artefacts ───────────────────────────────────
/target
/src-tauri/target
# Cargo registry caches that some IDE setups drop locally.
.cargo/
# Auto-generated by Tauri at build time (icons.rs, schemas/) — never
# hand-edited, regenerated on each `tauri dev|build`.
/src-tauri/gen
# Windows MSVC linker / debug residue that target/ usually contains
# but can leak elsewhere (e.g. when builds error out mid-link).
*.pdb
*.exp
*.lib
*.idb
# Rust coverage / profiling output.
*.profraw
coverage/

# ─── Frontend build / cache ─────────────────────────────────────────
# Covers BOTH the new Svelte frontend (frontend/) and the legacy
# Next.js frontend kept for reference (frontendMike/). node_modules and
# framework caches use **/ so the patterns survive directory renames.
**/node_modules/
**/.next/
**/.turbo/
**/.swc/
**/.parcel-cache/
**/.vite/
**/.svelte-kit/
**/.eslintcache
# Build output directories — anchored per known frontend dir to avoid
# matching an unrelated source folder that happens to be named dist/.
/frontend/out
/frontend/dist
/frontend/build
/frontend/.cache

# ─── Legacy React frontend — no longer part of the repository ───────
# frontendMike/ (the original Next.js/React frontend, derived from
# upstream willchen96/mike) has been fully replaced by the clean-room
# Svelte rewrite in frontend/. It is untracked and ignored; if a copy
# is still on disk it is for local reference only.
/frontendMike/
# Test-runner output (Vitest / Playwright).
**/playwright-report/
**/test-results/
**/.vitest/
# Vite bundle-analysis report.
**/stats.html
# TypeScript incremental build cache — wherever next/tsc drops it.
**/tsconfig.tsbuildinfo
*.tsbuildinfo

# ─── AI model + downloaded data ─────────────────────────────────────
# multilingual-e5-base ONNX weights (~1.1 GB) and tokenizer/configs.
# `ensure_fastembed_cache_dir()` pins these to %USERPROFILE%/mikerust-data
# but legacy / dev runs may leave them in either of these project paths.
.fastembed_cache/
mikerust-data/
# Generic catch-all for AI/ML caches that tools may drop in-repo.
.cache/
.huggingface/
.hf_cache/
**/huggingface_hub/
models/
*.onnx
*.safetensors
*.gguf
*.bin
*.pt
*.pth
# Compiled tokenizer files that fastembed downloads alongside the model.
tokenizer.json
spiece.model
sentencepiece.bpe.model

# ─── Application data ────────────────────────────────────────────────
# SQLite + storage tree (chats, indexed docs, FTS5 italian-corpus,
# EUR-Lex synced text, chat-attached docs cache, etc.).
#
# CRITICAL — DO NOT REMOVE: the runtime SQLite DB stores user API keys
# (Anthropic, Gemini, OpenAI) in plaintext. The patterns below are the
# primary safeguard against an accidental `git add .` ever pushing the
# DB to GitHub. The default DB location is `<user-home>/mikerust-data/`
# (outside the project tree) on purpose, but a clone with a custom
# DATABASE_URL could still land it inside the tree — `*.db` catches
# that.
data/
*.db
*.db-wal
*.db-shm
*.sqlite
*.sqlite3
# Italian-legal-corpus parquet shards if the importer was set to keep
# them on disk for a future refresh (it doesn't today, but be safe).
/data_corpora/
italian-legal-*.parquet

# ─── pdfium DLL ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Prebuilt platform-specific binary; README documents how to fetch.
libs/pdfium/
src-tauri/libs/pdfium/
# Setup archives downloaded from bblanchon/pdfium-binaries.
pdfium-*.tgz
pdfium-*.zip

# ─── onnxruntime DLLs ───────────────────────────────────────────────
# Same pattern as pdfium: the runtime libraries are NEVER committed,
# each contributor fetches the variant matching their target and EP
# selection. See libs/onnxruntime/README.md for the layout and
# download recipes. The directory structure (one subfolder per
# platform) IS tracked so the README is discoverable from git.
libs/onnxruntime/**/onnxruntime.dll
libs/onnxruntime/**/libonnxruntime.so
libs/onnxruntime/**/libonnxruntime.dylib
libs/onnxruntime/**/DirectML.dll
libs/onnxruntime/**/onnxruntime_providers_*.dll
libs/onnxruntime/**/Qnn*.dll
libs/onnxruntime/**/*.so.*
libs/onnxruntime/**/*.lib
libs/onnxruntime/**/*.pdb
libs/onnxruntime/**/*.exp
# Archives from microsoft/onnxruntime releases.
onnxruntime-*.tgz
onnxruntime-*.zip
onnxruntime-*.nupkg

# ─── Secrets ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local
**/.env.local
**/.env.*.local

# ─── Editor / OS ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.claude/
.vscode/
.idea/
.history/
*.swp
*.swo
*.bak
*.tmp
*.orig
*.rej
*.log
.DS_Store
.AppleDouble
.LSOverride
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini
ehthumbs.db

# ─── Ad-hoc planning notes ──────────────────────────────────────────
TODO.md

# ─── User-created runtime data ──────────────────────────────────────
# DOCX templates authored through the in-app editor. Runtime user data,
# not source; keeping it untracked also stops the `tauri dev` file
# watcher from rebuilding the app every time a template is saved.
config/docx-templates/user/

# Upstream Mike reference material (third-party docs from
# willchen96/mike + Semplifica adaptation notes) — kept on disk for
# author convenience but NOT shipped in this repo: those docs talk
# about a different stack and a different toolchain than MikeRust.
docs/mike-upstream/

# SuzieLaw reference checkout — a local clone of the SuzieLaw project
# used only to study its legal-source providers when porting corpus
# connectors. Third-party code; kept on disk for reference, never
# committed into this repo.
new_analysis/
